-- U.S.-based stock funds attract $7.6 bln over week - Lipper
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 04:52PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, July 31 (Reuters) - Investors in U.S.-based funds poured a net $7.6 billion into stock funds in the week ended July 30, marking their biggest inflows since June, data from Thomson Reuters' Lipper service showed on Thursday.

Emerging market stock funds attracted $1.2 billion, marking their biggest inflows since June. Taxable bond funds attracted $1.2 billion, marking their sixth straight week of inflows.